Product ID: IDY69100 ;

Data Parameters for 24 hours:
- Temperature (air) - Minimum and Maximum Temp  -daily, per site - 24 hours to 9am.
Recorded at 9 am local clock time. It is the highest (or lowest) temperature for the 24 hours leading up to the observation; and is recorded as the maximum temperature for the previous day, and minimum temperature for the day on which observation was made
- Rain - in the 24 hours to 9am on the date given;
- Evaporation - "Class A" pan evaporation in the 24 hours to 9am;
- Sunshine hours - Bright sunshine in the 24 hours to midnight of the date;
- Max Wind gust direction, speed and time -  of strongest gust in the 24 hours to midnight;
Parameters measured at 9am and 3pm local time:
Temperature, Relative Humidity, Cloud, Wind Direction & Spd (averaged over 10 minutes at time of Observation), and MSLP (Atmospheric pressure reduced to mean sea level)

See: [ http://www.bom.gov.au/climate/dwo/IDCJDW0000.shtml ], for more details, and units-of-measurement, per data parameter.

A snapshot of the website and data (containing the latest 14 months) is captured annually, and available from  PANDORA  (2003 onwards).

